Lucky Star ep24 impressions, we finishing now

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

[spoiler]no OP? blasphemy >_>

it's odd to think about how the US transfer student had to bring up the idea of cheerleaders at a pep rally kind of event... i guess they don't do the whole cheerleader thing in Japan as much as they do in the West

OOH EXTORTION :D

guh i hate it when they give me a crappy boobs joke and then right after they follow up with an actually good one... >_>

Kagami: GODDAMMIT WHY IS NOTHING ORGANIZED AROUND HERE

"we're so gonna die"

Kagami looks good in the haunted house outfit

oh god Akira is here

THAT SIGN.

aaand here we go with the OP, 18 minutes late :P

goddamn the feels no D:

your phone ruined everything, goddammit Minoru

i guess we don't get to see it in action for the final time, but whatever the rehearsal was good enough i guess, it would've been a bit redundant to do it twice

weird ED to finish off the series, whatever[/spoiler]

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

welp that's a wrap, i'd say it ended strongly but i think they could've done just a tiny bit better in some places to make it more fantastic

topics.body:
Some science news today cause I have to clean up before my family shows up today;

Scientists have confirmed that "reality doesn't exist until measured":http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2015/05/150527103110.htm in australia.

Dark solar cells have hit 20% efficiency.  While that's not as efficient as traditional solar cells the difference between the two is that dark solar cells work even when it's cloudy.  If solar cells hit say the 80% efficiency mark R.I.P. fossil fuels.

University of Utah has created photonic transistors and in the next three years there will be the first super computer to use this.  Basically what this means is *MUCH* faster computers than predicted in the next ten years; take how fast you think desktop computers will be in say ten years.. now square it.

"Australia has created a memory cell that can store information and process it at the same time.":http://www.rmit.edu.au/news/all-news/media-releases/2015/may/nano-memory-cell-can-mimic-long-term-memory/  Basically a computer cell that acts like a brain cell; basically the whole "a computer can't act like a brain" just got thrown out the window.
